# Copy this file to `.env`. It holds only non-secret config (PROVIDER, MODEL);
#
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# Your API key is NOT stored here or in .env — see the "API keys" note lower
# down and ../SECRETS.md. (.env is in .gitignore regardless; never commit it.)

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Which provider answers your questions.
#
#   mock    -> canned offline answer, no key, no cost
#   openai  -> OpenAI chat, streamed        (needs OPENAI_API_KEY)
#   claude  -> Claude messages, streamed    (needs ANTHROPIC_API_KEY)
#   local   -> a model via Ollama, on your machine (ext-local): no key, no
#              bill, nothing leaves the box. Needs Ollama running + two models:
#              `ollama pull qwen3:8b && ollama pull nomic-embed-text`.
#              `python check_setup.py` verifies both.
#
# Default is "mock" — the offline path always works.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
PROVIDER=mock

# --- Optional: local model knobs (PROVIDER=local) ---
# "local" is any OpenAI-compatible server — Ollama, LM Studio, llama.cpp,
# vLLM... — on this machine OR another. Point askrepo at it:
#   LOCAL_BASE_URL   full URL, used verbatim (another box / non-Ollama runner):
#                    e.g. http://192.168.1.106:1234/v1  (LM Studio's default port)
#   OLLAMA_HOST      host only, "/v1" appended — back-compat for a plain Ollama
#   (unset)          defaults to http://localhost:11434/v1
# LOCAL_MODEL / LOCAL_EMBED_MODEL pick the served model ids (defaults qwen3 /
# nomic-embed-text); check your runner's /v1/models list for the exact ids.
# LOCAL_API_KEY if the server/proxy wants a real bearer token (default: none).
# LOCAL_EMBED_BASE_URL / LOCAL_EMBED_API_KEY if embeddings live on a DIFFERENT
# endpoint than chat (a runner that serves chat but not embeddings).
# LOCAL_MAX_TOKENS answer budget (default 8192) — thinking models (qwen3,
# deepseek-r1) spend tokens reasoning first; raise it if answers come back blank.
# LOCAL_BASE_URL=http://192.168.1.106:1234/v1
# LOCAL_MODEL=unsloth/qwen3.6-35b-a3b
# LOCAL_EMBED_MODEL=text-embedding-qwen3-embedding-0.6b
#
# Pointing at another machine: bind the runner to 0.0.0.0 (not localhost) on
# that box, open the port in its firewall, and — over any untrusted network —
# put it behind TLS + a token (LOCAL_API_KEY). `python check_setup.py` verifies
# reachability + that both models are served.

# --- Optional: override the model for the active provider ---
# Defaults: gpt-4o-mini (openai) / claude-haiku-4-5 (claude) — the series'
# cheap-iteration picks; see ../MODELS.md for prices.
# MODEL=gpt-4o-mini

# --- Optional: hybrid retrieval blend (v03) ---
# Weight of vector search vs keyword (BM25): 1.0 = vector-only, 0.0 =
# keyword-only. A knob to measure (v04), not a truth. Default 0.7.
# BLEND=0.7

# --- Optional: per-session spend ceiling in USD (v07) ---
# A session budget the tool refuses to blow through (0 = unlimited). Most
# visible in a multi-call session: `run_evals.py --budget 0.01` stops the run
# before exceeding it rather than quietly running up the bill.
# BUDGET=0

# Structured logs: set ASKREPO_LOG=info (in the environment, not here) to emit
# one JSON trace line per request — trace_id, spans, tokens, cost, cache hit —
# that reconstructs the request after the fact. Off by default.

# Embeddings: PROVIDER=openai embeds with text-embedding-3-small;
# PROVIDER=claude embeds with Voyage voyage-3.5 (needs VOYAGE_API_KEY —
# Anthropic has no first-party embeddings model; see ../MODELS.md).

# --- API keys are NOT stored here ---
# Your key never goes in this file or in .env. Store it in your OS keychain and
# inject it per-command with `secrun` (2-minute setup: ../SECRETS.md), then run
# key-using commands as:  secrun python -m askrepo ask "..."
#   PROVIDER=openai  needs  OPENAI_API_KEY     https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
#   PROVIDER=claude  needs  ANTHROPIC_API_KEY  https://console.anthropic.com/settings/keys
